<TITLE> 100 upazilas will see elections in May: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khulna, March 5 (bdnews24.com)Local government adviser Anwarul Iqbal said Wednesday that elections to upazilas, city corporations and seven municipalities would be held ahead of Jatiya Sangsad elections. The adviser said the elections to 100 upazilas would be held in May, preceded by the elections to four city corporations in April. Voter registration in 80 of the upazilas where elections would be held has been completed, Iqbal said, speaking as chief guest at the inauguration of Khulna WASA at a programme at the Khulna City Corporation. Acting Khulna City mayor Md Moniruzzaman Moni and Khulna WASA's managing director Shamima Sultana were also present. The adviser also focused on the troubled jute industry which he said must be saved. "The government considers giving special loans to jute growers," he said. According to the adviser, a textile institute will be set up in the once-vibrant industrial city of Khulna. After the inauguration, Iqbal exchanged views with the representatives of civil society at the Khulna Deputy Commissioner's Office at 11 am. bdnews2
